    "Body": " Overseas Crime and Intelligence Data Analyst Love Justice International - Denver, CO Quick Apply Job Details Full-timeEstimated: $45,000 - $66,000 a year5 hours ago Qualifications Military Intelligence Military Experience Law Enforcement GIS Analysis Skills Bachelor's Degree Full Job Description PLEASE NOTE: This position is support-raised and based in South Asia. Please do not submit your resume through this posting. You can apply directly at https://www.lovejustice.ngo/apply. About Us: Love Justice International (LJI) is a Christian nonprofit organization compelled by God\u2019s love to fight the world\u2019s greatest injustices. We fight injustice in two primary ways: through our expanding anti-human trafficking work and by caring for orphaned and abandoned children. We currently work throughout Asia and Africa. * Position Type: Full Time, Support-Raised*, Overseas (Asia) If hired, the candidate will be required to raise financial support to cover his/her own salary, benefits, and expenses. Raising support is a key example of the body of Christ supporting its members and joining in the fight against injustice. LJI will provide administrative and prayer support throughout the process, as well as guidance and resources to build up a support base. Please prayerfully consider whether you may be called to step out in faith and raise support for this position. Position Overview: LJI's anti-human trafficking model focuses on transit monitoring. We identify, intercept, and assist trafficking victims as they are being transported\u2014when victims and traffickers are the most visible and open to detection\u2014and before they reach the destination where victims will be sold, hidden, and abused. Because the crime of trafficking has already commenced, we have access to actionable intelligence to apprehend suspects and understand trafficking methods. We have intercepted over 21,000 individuals to prevent them from being trafficked, and we have helped convict over 100 traffickers. LJI is seeking a Crime and Intelligence Data Analyst to gather, collate, analyze, disseminate, and evaluate data from various internal and external sources to support its work around the world. This position will research, assemble, and present information in order to provide investigative leads and determine developing patterns and trends and any changes in criminal activity to increase the effectiveness of LJI\u2019s investigative staff and its partner organizations. This work requires the use of various analytical methods, including: intercept and investigative report analysis, social media platform analysis, graphic presentation of data, charting of events in chronological sequence, and collection and consolidation of intelligence data from other sources to produce strategic, tactical, operational and analytical products. The Crime and Intelligence Data Analyst will be expected to prepare and disseminate timely and relevant reports that enhance the ability of LJI to adequately identify and effectively respond to both emerging and long-term issues. The successful candidate for the C&I Data Analyst position will understand the importance of crime analysis and its supporting roles, will be able to work collaboratively in a highly data-driven organization, and will possess a strong working knowledge of the theories, principles, and practice of intelligence and crime analysis to include the strategic, tactical, investigative, and administrative aspects. Additionally, the ideal candidate will be well versed in a variety of analytical software tools and geographic information systems used to accurately produce reports, identify trends, and support investigations and monitoring operations. This position is based in South Asia and reports to the Vice President of Asia Anti-Trafficking, with additional oversight from the Chief Investigations and Security Officer. Primary Duties and Responsibilities: Reviewing and analyzing interception and investigative reports and other data Identifying trends, patterns, modus operandi, and changes in criminal activity Performing intelligence analysis by gathering information from internal and external sources about people involved in crimes, repeat victims, and criminal organizations and networks and ensuring the information is properly analyzed, evaluated, and stored for effective retrieval and dissemination Performing strategic administrative and operational analysis by developing, maintaining, and analyzing LJI resources to provide guidance on monitoring, investigative, and prevention strategies and policies Conducting special projects and presenting unbiased data based solely on statistical information Determining criminal associations and patterns of criminal activity relating to specific offenders or groups of offenders Conducting background research on suspects or criminals and maintaining records on certain repeat criminal offenders to recognize modus operandi Providing relevant information to transit monitors and investigations personnel Preparing comprehensive analytical products such as reports, charts, graphs, tables, and maps Compiling and disseminating bulletins summarizing current activity regarding suspects, known offenders, trends and other information Providing attention to detail when authoring bulletins to ensure accuracy of information and grammar Coordinating the exchange of bulletins and other information between outside law enforcement and partner organizations Qualifications: Mature Christian faith A strong commitment to social justice and advocacy on behalf of vulnerable populations Ability to work well in cross-cultural contexts and sensitivity to different cultures Critical-thinking and problem-solving skills Strong work ethic, self-motivation, and willingness to adapt to changing and challenging circumstances A bachelor's degree in Criminal Justice, Public Administration, Computer Science, Statistics, or another related field from an accredited university, two years of related experience and/or training, or an equivalent combination of education and experience Experience in criminal intelligence, crime analysis, or military intelligence or similar analytical experience in a law enforcement capacity can substitute on a year-for-year basis for the required college education Two years of experience with law enforcement or any equivalent combination of education and experience which would provide the knowledge, skills, and abilities required for this position is preferred Desired: Certification by the International Association of Crime Analysts or the International Association of Law Enforcement Intelligence Analysts * Job Type: Full-time Experience: Crime Analysis: 2 years (Preferred) Law Enforcement: 2 years (Preferred) Education: Bachelor's (Preferred) Work Location: Multiple locations Schedule: Monday to Friday Company's website: lovejustice.ngo ",
